# Naming conventions

## Files and folders

| Kind | Pattern | Examples |
|------|---------|----------|
| Route screens | **PascalCase** + `Page` | `SitesPage.tsx`, `AlertsPage.tsx` |
| Reusable UI | **PascalCase** | `ThemeSelect.tsx`, `PileCard.tsx` |
| Root shell | **PascalCase** | `App.tsx` |
| Entry | **kebab-case** or conventional | `main.tsx`, `index.css` |
| Hooks | **camelCase**, `use` prefix | `useTheme.ts` |
| Context / providers | **PascalCase** for provider file | `ThemeProvider.tsx` |
| Plain modules (no component) | **camelCase** | `mockData.ts`, `themeShared.ts`, `context.ts` |
| Domain types (per file) | **lowercase** domain noun | `sensor.ts`, `pile.ts`, `alert.ts`, `theme.ts` |
| Type barrel | `index.ts` | Re-exports only |

New folders under `src/` should stay **lowercase** (`pages`, `types`, `data`, `theme`, `components`).

## React

- **Default export** for page and feature components; name should **match the filename** (e.g. file `ThemeSelect.tsx` → `export default function ThemeSelect`).
- **Props** type: `ComponentNameProps` (e.g. `ThemeSelectProps`) when you need an explicit type.
- **Event handlers**: name with **`handle` + purpose** — `handlePileSelect`, `handleThemeChange`, `handlePileListClick`. Define with **`useCallback`** (or module-level + delegation) — **never** `onClick={() => doThing(id)}` inline in JSX (recreated every render).
- **Class name / style helpers** (not components): **`get` + noun + `ClassName`** — `getNavLinkClassName` (may live at module scope for a stable reference to `NavLink`).

## TypeScript symbols

- **Interfaces / type aliases** for domain models: **PascalCase** — `PileMock`, `SensorReading`, `OperatorAlert`, `ThemePreference`.
- **Union members** for fixed sets: match domain vocabulary — `'OK' | 'Warning' | 'Critical'`, `'bottom' | 'middle' | 'top'`.
- **Functions** (including getters): **camelCase** — `getPiles`, `getPileById`, `resolveTheme`, `buildSensors`.
- **Boolean** variables: **`is` / `has` / `should`** — `isActive`, `hasAlerts`, `shouldRefetch`.
- **Constants** (immutable, module-level): **SCREAMING_SNAKE** — `THEME_STORAGE_KEY`, `MOCK_PILES`. Prefer one object or `as const` for grouped config if it reads better.

## Domain (agriQ)

- **Sensor IDs**: assignment format **`S01`–`S30`** (zero-padded), stored as **strings**.
- **Pile slugs / route ids**: **kebab-case** — `emek-north`, `emek-south` (match `PileMock.id`).
- **User-facing labels**: **Title Case** or sentence case per product copy — e.g. “Emek North”, “What to do next”.

## Imports

- Prefer **named `import type`** for types from `src/types` — keeps value vs type imports obvious.
- Avoid default-exporting types from `mockData.ts`; types come from **`src/types`**.

## What to avoid

- Abbreviated cryptic names (`mgr`, `tmp2`) in anything but the shortest loop indices.
- **Generic** file names (`utils.ts`, `helpers.ts`) unless the folder already scopes them; prefer `themeShared.ts`-style specificity.
